description.narrative: 2021 has seen exponential growth in advocacy, media, digital and brand performance as UNICEF India strategically utilized opportunities in crisis. The RCCE response to the pandemic intensified through India’s devastating second wave, extraordinary support to GoI in the LargestVaccineDrive, cutting edge communication in addressing risk perceptions, promoting healthy practices, vaccines uptake, while countering misinformation, hesitancy. Creative content, campaigns in own channels have outdone earlier KPIs with 86 percent positive coverage in the media; 6 billion reach, 62 million engagements, and 200 million video views, 8.5 billion impressions in digital. Over 70 MPs were engaged in legislative advocacy with remarkable advocacy | Status:On-track | As-of Date:08/01/2022
